<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.10061422>
    dc:description "FIGURES 1–2. Generalized external morphology of Omophoita. (1) Dorsal view. (2) Ventral view. (SCP), scape; (ACL), antennal callus; (EYE), eye; (VRT), vertex; (FRI), inflated frons; (LAB), labrum; (PRN), pronotum; (HPC), hypomeral callus; (PRP), prosternal process; (SCT), scutellum; (ELT), elytra; (EPL), epipleura; (MST), mesothorax; (MTT), metathorax; (MTF), metafemur; (MTI), metatibia; (RAM), apical escavation of the metatibia; (MTS), metatibial spur; (MTA), metatarsos; (CLW), claws; (VAS), visible abdominal sclerites (sternite)." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/10061422/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

